Properties

Filter Filter

Edit

Gets or sets the OData $filter expression to apply to the suggestions query.

public string Filter { get; set; }Public Property Filter As String
Value
String String

Fuzzy Fuzzy

Edit

Gets or sets a value indicating whether to use fuzzy matching for the suggestion query. Default is false. when set to true, the query will find suggestions even if there's a substituted or missing character in the search text. While this provides a better experience in some scenarios it comes at a performance cost as fuzzy suggestion searches are slower and consume more resources.

public bool ? Fuzzy { get; set; }Public Property Fuzzy As Boolean?
Value
Nullable<Boolean> Nullable(Of Boolean)

HighlightPostTag HighlightPostTag

Edit

Gets or sets a string tag that is appended to hit highlights. Must be set with HighlightPreTag. If omitted, hit highlighting of suggestions is disabled.

public string HighlightPostTag { get; set; }Public Property HighlightPostTag As String
Value
String String

HighlightPreTag HighlightPreTag

Edit

Gets or sets a string tag that is prepended to hit highlights. Must be set with HighlightPostTag. If omitted, hit highlighting of suggestions is disabled.

public string HighlightPreTag { get; set; }Public Property HighlightPreTag As String
Value
String String

MinimumCoverage MinimumCoverage

Edit

Gets or sets a number between 0 and 100 indicating the percentage of the index that must be covered by a suggestion query in order for the query to be reported as a success. This parameter can be useful for ensuring search availability even for services with only one replica. The default is 80.

public double ? MinimumCoverage { get; set; }Public Property MinimumCoverage As Double?
Value
Nullable<Double> Nullable(Of Double)

OrderBy OrderBy

Edit

Gets or sets the comma-separated list of OData $orderby expressions by which to sort the results. Each expression can be either a field name or a call to the geo.distance() function. Each expression can be followed by asc to indicate ascending, and desc to indicate descending. The default is ascending order. Ties will be broken by the match scores of documents. If no OrderBy is specified, the default sort order is descending by document match score. There can be at most 32 Orderby clauses.

public string OrderBy { get; set; }Public Property OrderBy As String
Value
String String

Search Search

Edit

Gets or sets the search text on which to base suggestions.

public string Search { get; set; }Public Property Search As String
Value
String String

SearchFields SearchFields

Edit

Gets or sets the comma-separated list of field names to consider when querying for suggestions.

public string SearchFields { get; set; }Public Property SearchFields As String
Value
String String

Select Select

Edit

Gets or sets the comma-separated list of fields to retrieve. If unspecified, all fields marked as retrievable in the schema are included.

public string Select { get; set; }Public Property Select As String
Value
String String

SuggesterName SuggesterName

Edit

Gets or sets the name of the suggester as specified in the suggesters collection that's part of the index definition.

public string SuggesterName { get; set; }Public Property SuggesterName As String
Value
String String

Top Top

Edit

Gets or sets the number of suggestions to retrieve. This must be a value between 1 and 100. The default is to 5.

public int ? Top { get; set; }Public Property Top As Integer?
Value
Nullable<Int32> Nullable(Of Int32)
